Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.43,0:15:15.43,Episode Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\p1\c&H167C8A&\fscx99\fscy94\pos(383.143,184.286)}m 263 187 l 1025 187 1000 363 286 363
Dialogue: 9,0:15:18.56,0:15:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 9,0:15:19.39,0:15:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, what is it?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:21.90,0:15:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:22.94,0:15:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm bad with kids.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:24.61,0:15:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:25.82,0:15:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo-san, could you spare a moment?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:30.36,0:15:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to see the main building.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:33.03,0:15:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The main building?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:34.49,0:15:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:35.53,0:15:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking into the hanged shadow.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:39.33,0:15:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you show us to room seven?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:42.50,0:15:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I can't right now.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:44.71,0:15:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Onee-chan will get mad at me.{HNNNNNNNNNNNNGGGGGG}
Dialogue: 9,0:15:48.30,0:15:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then at least tell us this.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:50.01,0:15:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that room still used for guests?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:53.55,0:15:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Guests only use the bath and the dining hall in the main building.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:58.68,0:16:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's an empty room.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:00.06,0:16:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second floor is used for storage.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:03.56,0:16:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I go now?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:05.81,0:16:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:07.19,0:16:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were very helpf—
Dialogue: 9,0:16:09.07,0:16:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't like me.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:11.11,0:16:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. I'm sure she's just scared of big men.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:15.03,0:16:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So cute!
Dialogue: 9,0:16:18.24,0:16:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a problem if we can't see room seven?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:20.91,0:16:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not so much a problem as it is a hassle.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:23.12,0:16:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't see the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:25.42,0:16:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:26.50,0:16:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These bring back memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.34,0:16:28.59,Open,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fay-0.15\fax0.5\blur1\fs60\fnBurst My Bubble\b1\c&H222525&\frz359.5\pos(916.8,242.051)}Rie{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.13,0:16:32.26,Open,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fay-0.15\fax0.15\blur1\fs60\fnBurst My Bubble\b1\c&H252A46&\frz359.5\frx358\fry26\pos(1008.69,397.022)}Rie{\b0}
Dialogue: 9,0:16:33.76,0:16:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning radio exercises...
Dialogue: 9,0:16:35.59,0:16:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't gone to those in two years!
Dialogue: 9,0:16:38.68,0:16:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You went until second year of middle school?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.76,0:16:42.18,Sheet,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fnFansub Block\pos(646.286,219.46)\fscx92\fscy100\c&H9CCBC6&}AAAAA
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.76,0:16:42.18,Sheet,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fnCorbel\b1\frx358\fry358\fscx73\fscy100\pos(646.317,218.397)\c&H123935&} Seizansou Annex{\b0}
Dialogue: 9,0:16:40.60,0:16:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:43.98,0:16:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take a look from the back.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:47.94,0:16:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did it rain last night?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:50.57,0:16:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was a passing shower.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:52.57,0:16:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To see a shadow against the light, both the east and west windows had to be open.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:59.99,0:17:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 9,0:17:02.20,0:17:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for lunch.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:06.04,0:17:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for the meal.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:11.96,0:17:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be wonderful to have a sister.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:15.30,0:17:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Did you wish you had a sister?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:18.43,0:17:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kind of.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:19.47,0:17:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, did you figure anything out?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:21.31,0:17:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:21.76,0:17:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're still just starting to look into it.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:23.60,0:17:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I do have a theory.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:25.39,0:17:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Let's hear it.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:29.15,0:17:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:30.27,0:17:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:32.03,0:17:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you guys leaving me out of the loop?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:34.15,0:17:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Out of the loop or in, where the heck do you go all day?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:37.74,0:17:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see you at all!
Dialogue: 9,0:17:38.53,0:17:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get it, do you?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:40.66,0:17:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're supposed to use a hot spring multiple times a day.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:43.08,0:17:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how it works?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:44.50,0:17:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ta-da!
Dialogue: 9,0:17:45.66,0:17:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:46.25,0:17:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't my yukata cute?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:47.71,0:17:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's wonderful!
Dialogue: 9,0:17:48.92,0:17:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look great!
Dialogue: 9,0:17:50.38,0:17:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got my parents to buy it for me at the start of summer break!
Dialogue: 9,0:17:53.42,0:17:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You always said you wanted one.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:55.01,0:17:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pattern is good.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:56.34,0:17:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's bad?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:58.05,0:17:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The obi.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:59.89,0:18:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an imitation.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:01.10,0:18:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt it's radioactive.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:02.81,0:18:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said "imitation", not "mutation".
Dialogue: 9,0:18:05.85,0:18:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The butterfly is a separate part from the obi.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:09.02,0:18:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't rightfully call that a yukata.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:11.15,0:18:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More useless information.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:17.03,0:18:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:19.99,0:18:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I've been cursed by the hanged shadow too?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:30.21,0:18:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to the hot spring again today.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:32.38,0:18:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 9,0:18:33.63,0:18:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hanged shadow.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:36.21,0:18:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A product of Ibara and Chitanda's fevered minds.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:40.18,0:18:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Withered flowers.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:42.26,0:18:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But something is missing.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:49.52,0:18:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back together.{She knows what's up.}
Dialogue: 9,0:18:52.65,0:18:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:56.40,0:18:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't you just at the dining hall?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:59.95,0:19:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get here?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:01.28,0:19:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you see, if you slide down the slope behind Seizansou, you come out right behind here.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:05.99,0:19:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll slide down a mountain for a shortcut?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:09.62,0:19:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Typical Satoshi behavior.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:15.50,0:19:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't think of anything that would appease Chitanda.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:19.88,0:19:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Explaining the shadow is simple.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:22.05,0:19:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The question is, why?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:26.51,0:19:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou, did you get dizzy again?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:28.60,0:19:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, were there any events last night?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:32.06,0:19:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got dizzy in the bath.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:33.69,0:19:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything {\i1}else{\i0}?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:35.98,0:19:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We all told ghost stories together.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:37.69,0:19:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had more flowers than hands.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:39.61,0:19:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I meant anything official.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:41.99,0:19:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there was the summer festival.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:44.12,0:19:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you hear the drums?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:46.37,0:19:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drums?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:48.37,0:19:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:49.79,0:19:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The summer festival!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:51.50,0:19:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see now...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:53.04,0:19:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what about it?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:02.38,0:20:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That shadow you saw...
Dialogue: 9,0:20:04.30,0:20:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was probably just a yukata on a hanger.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:11.93,0:20:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would it be hung there?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:14.19,0:20:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And why would someone open the windows specifically so we could see it hanging?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:18.44,0:20:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:18.86,0:20:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't so you could see it.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:21.36,0:20:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 9,0:20:22.40,0:20:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was to dry it.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:24.20,0:20:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The yukata was wet.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:25.99,0:20:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The windows were open to let the wind in so it would dry faster.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:30.75,0:20:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:32.33,0:20:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it rained.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:33.66,0:20:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I mean, why was it hanging in room seven?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:36.63,0:20:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So no one could see it being dried.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:40.42,0:20:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we saw it!
Dialogue: 9,0:20:42.01,0:20:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:42.76,0:20:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To hide it from the rest of the family.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:45.43,0:20:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:47.26,0:20:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who hung it up to dry was Kayo.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:51.22,0:20:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo was envious of Rie's yukata and wanted to try it on.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:55.06,0:20:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure Rie wouldn't lend it to her.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:57.15,0:20:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not? They're sisters...
Dialogue: 9,0:20:59.61,0:21:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you notice?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:01.07,0:21:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rie wrote her name on her cup, stamp card, and ball.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:04.57,0:21:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She makes sure everyone knows what's hers.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:08.03,0:21:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo probably couldn't ask Rie to lend her the yukata.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:11.74,0:21:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then...
Dialogue: 9,0:21:13.79,0:21:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, Kayo wanted to wear it.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:15.79,0:21:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she secretly took it and wore it to the summer festival last night.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:19.92,0:21:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She left around eight o'clock.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:22.00,0:21:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo-san went to the summer festival?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:24.05,0:21:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw her.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:25.26,0:21:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I noticed someone leaving the house last night.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:30.60,0:21:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't sound like Kayo was around for the ghost stories, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:33.39,0:21:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, she wasn't there.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:36.10,0:21:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around that time, Kayo ran into trouble at the festival.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:40.11,0:21:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It started raining.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:42.78,0:21:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't last long, but the yukata was soaked.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:46.11,0:21:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo remembered that they were going to play with fireworks the next day.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:49.37,0:21:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She knew that Rie was planning to wear that yukata then.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:53.37,0:21:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had to find a way to dry the yukata in time before Rie found out.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:57.71,0:22:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The family uses the first floor of the main building, and the annex was out of the question.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:01.79,0:22:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She couldn't use the dryer that late at night, either.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:03.96,0:22:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, when everyone was asleep,
Dialogue: 9,0:22:07.55,0:22:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she snuck into the most distant room in the main building and hung the yukata up to dry.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:11.18,0:22:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But bad luck befell her again.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:14.18,0:22:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the windows open, the moonlight made it look like a hanged shadow.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:20.06,0:22:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And even worse, we began to look into it.
Dialogue: 1,0:22:20.81,0:22:21.40,Sheet,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1.5\fn5\fs150\fnCorbel\b1\c&H1D2963&\frx350\fry0\pos(636.886,344.543)\frz0.1232}No Entry{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.81,0:22:21.40,Episode Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\p1\c&H308C94&\fscx99\fscy94\pos(383.143,184.286)}m 263 187 l 1025 187 1000 363 286 363
Dialogue: 9,0:22:25.32,0:22:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Kayo felt like she was being cornered.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:27.82,0:22:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet the shadow behind the door was Kayo, too.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:33.03,0:22:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo-san...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:34.91,0:22:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She returned the yukata early in the morning.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:38.08,0:22:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike Rie, she goes to morning exercises every day, so putting it back was easy.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:45.34,0:22:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:47.01,0:22:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should probably keep this from Ibara.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:49.59,0:22:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's better not to spark any trouble in the family.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:54.26,0:22:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:56.97,0:23:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that would mean those two don't get along.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:02.27,0:23:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't lend a yukata to your own sister...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:13.49,0:23:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty normal. Siblings—
Dialogue: 9,0:23:16.08,0:23:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always wanted a sibling.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:19.58,0:23:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An older sister I could look up to, or a cute little brother.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:28.05,0:23:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The siblings Chitanda imagines...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:31.76,0:23:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,may just be withered flowers.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:36.85,0:23:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hot...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:42.06,0:23:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:43.27,0:23:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:56.49,0:24:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe not {\i1}just{\i0} withered flowers.
